From eric Eric Trepanier Subject Why I'm not using Dos anymore In article writes Regarding the horror stories about DOUBLEDISK and STACKER killing hard drives I was wondering if the dos MIRROR command works on the doubled drive info as well as the normal fat table and partition If it records the vital DoubleDisk info then using it daily should go a long way toward protecting yourself against the type of catastrophic failure If it doesn't then shame on MIRROR is one of those DOS commands that didn't survive the change from DOS It's been dropped along with BACKUP JOIN EDLIN and a couple other crummy old DOS You can still use the commands if you absolutely have to but they are not included on the distribution However in MIRROR's case I'm certain that it does not know anything about DoubleSpaced Eric Eric Trepanier Internet eric CI Grenon Laval Quebec Everybody has a right to believe in something Canada I believe I'll have another beer